ary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Of Germanic origin (via French  <b>Adélaïde</b> ), from <i>adal</i> ‘noble’ + <i>heid</i> ‘kind, sort’. It was borne in the 10th century by the wife of the Holy Roman Emperor Otto the Great. She became regent after his death and was revered as a saint. The given name increased in popularity in England during the 19th century, when it was borne by the wife of King William IV; she was the daughter of the ruler of the German duchy of Saxe-Meiningen. The Australian city of Adelaide was named in her honour."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Adelaise de Essex was born in 1122, in Essex, England, United Kingdom as the daughter of De Essex. She had at least 1 son with Ranulf de La Haye. She died in 1145, at the age of 23."},"et":{"1122–1145":"1122–1145","1120–Male":"1120–Surnud","1145–1188":"1145–1188","–Male":"Surnud","1145":"1145","1122":"1122","1188":"1188","1120":"1120","Cambridge, Cambridgeshire, England, United Kingdom":"Cambridge, Cambridgeshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Essex, England":"Essex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1122–1145":"1122–1145","1120–Male":"1120–Kuollut","1145–1188":"1145–1188","–Male":"Kuollut","1145":"1145","1122":"1122","1188":"1188","1120":"1120","Cambridge, Cambridgeshire, England, United Kingdom":"Cambridge, Cambridgeshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Essex, England":"Essex, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1122–1145":"1122–1145","1120–Male":"1120–Décédé","1145–1188":"1145–1188","–Male":"Décédé","1145":"1145","1122":"1122","1188":"1188","1120":"1120","Cambridge, Cambridgeshire, England, United Kingdom":"Canteburge, Cambridgeshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Essex, England":"Essex, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Adelaise d’Essex est née en 1122, à Essex, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni, fille de De Essex. Elle a eu au moins 1 fils avec Ranulf de La Haye. Elle est décédée en 1145, à l’âge de 23 ans."},"de":{"1122–1145":"1122–1145","11